    },
    {
      "text": "America Daitōryō Senkyo (Japanese: アメリカ大統領選挙, Hepburn: Amerika Daitōryō Senkyo; translated as United States Presidential Race on the manual and cartridge label and misspelled United State Presidential Race on the box) is a government simulation video game released by Hector Playing Interface for the Family Computer in 1988. It is loosely based on the 1988 election campaign for the president of the United States and features characters based on actual candidates and other politicians. The game was conceived and directed by Japanese CNN Daywatch newscaster  Shintaro Ito, who would later become a politician himself.",
